parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of power, inability to shift gears, and loss of control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
4-Wheel drive system failure can cause distractions to the consumer, leading to accidents or loss of control.
Inaccurate speedometer readings can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause loud noises, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the vehicle
broken exhaust manifold bolts or studs
exhaust noise that changes with engine temperature.
